            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-124-person1295">
                  SOPHIA 
                  LOUISA LEWIS
               <interp inst="t18331128-124-person1295" type="surname" value="LOUISA LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-124-person1295" type="given" value="SOPHIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-124-person1295" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18331128-124-viclabel703" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-124-victim1294 t18331128-124-viclabel703"></join>. The prisoner lodged in my house in <placeName id="t18331128-124-crimeloc704">King-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-124-crimeloc704" type="placeName" value="King-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-124-crimeloc704" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-124-off701 t18331128-124-crimeloc704"></join>, for seven weeks; a young man came first and took the lodging for himself and his wife; the prisoner came the same evening - they lodged there for seven weeks; they were to pay me 7s. a week, but they only paid for one week - the young man had been to sea, and he said he was looking for a situation - the property stated is part of what was let to them with the room - I went into the room in consequence of what I heard - I said to the young man, "I understand I am to be robbed; let me see what is gone" - I then missed these articles; they told me they were gone, and the duplicates were in the room; I had never permitted them to pawn them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. What did you say to the prisoner? A. I said, "I have been a mother to you, you will steal my bed next" - she said, "I should not stand nice about it" - I lent the prisoner my son's jacket to pawn, because she cried, and said she was in the family way and wanted to be married; I lent it her to get asked in church: I did not then know that she was married to another man, but I find she is - it was about a fortnight before they left me, that I lent her the jacket; she said she did not know how she should get married, and I said I would lend her my ring as she had not got one - I never lent her the things mentioned in this indictment, and she never told me she had pawned them till I went into the room - while I went for a policeman, I am told the man got out at the window, and the prisoner went out at the door - when I returned with the officer, I found the duplicates in the room; the prisoner came back and said, "I am the person who robbed you; I have come to give myself up."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-124-person1296">
                  HENRY 
                  JOHN BRITTAIN
